        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-10-29 07:01:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAndreas, do you think we should land this patch to b2_1, or just as a temporary solution to ask the customer to apply it directly?\n\nThe completely solution should be back porting OI scrub, which is in processing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b54ac03eaee13df77e2a225dcecfcbb67fed465b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-29 07:45:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think this patch is valuable to land to b2_1 even if OI scrub is back ported for 2.1.4. Firstly, it solves an important problem that would prevent the MDT from starting even if OI scrub was working. Secondly, it isn't totally clear if OI scrub will land for 2.1.4 or not.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "a4019d37b3b5a5c4a920b77eab29a3aee7a6240a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-10-30 21:16:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOleg, would you please to consider to land this to b2_1? thanks!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
